        ```
    *   **Hooking `zzafh` (the Iterable)**: Hooking `zzafh.iterator()` could reveal when an iterator is requested from the iterable and potentially what state `zzafh` holds when creating the iterator.
        ```javascript
        Java.perform(function() {
            var zzafh = Java.use('com.google.android.libraries.places.internal.zzafh');
            zzafh.iterator.implementation = function() {
                var iterator = this.iterator();
